  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-e0831fbb-7fff-7175-5aa8-1bc7881d5215\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">This dust is made of powdered gemstones, and can be added to the material components of certain spells to extend their effects. The dust has been tested in various forms of circle magic, and is known to have the following uses. However, it may have other useful applications as well. Only experimentation can tell.</span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:bold;font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Circle of Death</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">: When mixed with the powdered pearl of a Circle of Death spell, the sphere of negative energy lingers in the air when cast. Until your next turn, any creature other than you that enters or begins its turn in the sphere suffers the effects of the spell again.</span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:bold;font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Magic Circle</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">: When mixed with the other components of a Magic Circle spell, the duration of the spell is doubled.</span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:bold;font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Teleportation Circle</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">: When mixed with the ink of a teleportation circle spell, the circle is not consumed instantly when the spell is cast. Instead, the circle fades slowly over the course of 2d4 days. Until it fades completely, it may be used as a destination for future castings of Teleportation Circle as if it was a permanent circle.</span></p>",
